{
  "texts": [
    "In doing so, VOSviewer utilizes a smart local moving algorithm (Waltman and Van Eck 2013).",
    "Therefore, network analyses were performed using VOSviewer software.",
    "The figures or network diagrams generated through VOSviewer use clustering procedures to allot articles with higher strengths to create results (networks) displayed in different colors.",
    "As described earlier, nodes or items represent authors, documents, keywords, etc., and their size signifies highly cited or co-cited literature.",
    "Edges represent relations in which the closeness of two nodes indicates a higher strength of the items (e.g., authors) and the co-citations or relations between them."
  ]
}